<br>
I also watched another guild do Cazic Thulle (the diety, however you spell it), and as part of their pre-kill buff session, their mages made TRods for everyone, dropped them, and everyone took one. Melee dropped their rods before the fight (named, single target engagement raid so able to time when and where), and other casters halfway through the fight. Mages were nuking and pets engaged the entire fight, and I don't think there was a single call for more TRods (in fact, there were spares left over once the kill was made). Now, of course, I have no idea how CT relates to big ToV dragons, but this is the beauty of Mage 'buffing'. Persistance until logging or use of the item.<br>
<br>
